text: Kim Ja-ok (October 11, 1951 - November 16, 2014) was a South Korean actress. Kim was born in Busan, South Korea. She was known for her roles in Like Land and Sky, My Tutor Friend, Jeni, Juno, The Righteous Thief, and in Nobody's Daughter Haewon. Ja-ok died in Seoul, South Korea from lung cancer, aged 63. ==References== ==Other websites== * Category:1951 births Category:2014 deaths Category:Deaths from lung cancer Category:Cancer deaths in South Korea Category:South Korean movie actors Category:South Korean television actors
